# Code Style and Conventions

## Code Formatting

The project uses multiple tools to ensure consistent code style:

1. Prettier for basic code formatting - See [.prettierrc.js](mdc:.prettierrc.js)
2. ESLint for JavaScript/TypeScript linting - See [eslint.config.mjs](mdc:eslint.config.mjs)
3. Biome for additional code quality checks - See [biome.jsonc](mdc:biome.jsonc)
4. EditorConfig for editor consistency - See [.editorconfig](mdc:.editorconfig)

## Git Conventions

- Git attributes are defined in [.gitattributes](mdc:.gitattributes)
- Commit messages are linted using commitlint - See [commitlint.config.js](mdc:commitlint.config.js)
- Pre-commit hooks are managed by Husky in the `.husky` directory

## TypeScript Configuration

The TypeScript configuration is managed in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json), which serves as the base configuration for all TypeScript projects in the monorepo.
